article.headline: Illinois State 82, Creighton 77 (OT)
article.story: OMAHA, Neb. (AP) -- Trey Guidry scored a career-high 30 points, lifting Illinois State to an 82-77 victory over Creighton in overtime Saturday night, ending an eight-game losing streak to the Bluejays. Illinois State (13-5, 5-3 Missouri Valley Conference) hadn't beaten Creighton (12-7, 4-4) since Jan. 8, 2001, and didn't appear ready to end the losing streak when Creighton made its first six shots and 10 of its first 12. But Illinois State was down only 37-32 at halftime thanks to Guidry's scoring. Lorenzo George added 19 points and Vince Greene 10 for Illinois State, which used an 8-0 run to take a 77-71 lead in the 5-minute extra period. Nate Funk led Creighton with 26 points, tying his career high. Kellen Miliner added 13 points and Tyler McKinney 12. Illinois State trailed the entire first half before rallying behind Guidry to lead 47-45 with 15:51 to play. Guidry, who scored 18 points in the first half to keep the Redbirds close, also made the shot to put them ahead. It was his first basket of the second half, but by then he was getting scoring help from several teammates. The Bluejays used a 9-2 run, highlighted by Pierce Hibma's 3-pointer, to lead 68-62 with 1:57 left in regulation. But Illinois State scored the final six points, capped by Guidry's 3-pointer with 4 seconds left, to force overtime. The Redbirds took the lead on a free throw by Gregg Alexander only to have Creighton go ahead 71-69 on a 3-pointer by McKinney, who had missed the front end of the bonus with a minute left in regulation with a chance to put his team up by seven. Then Gordon, the conference's top scorer, took control, scoring on two layups to regain the lead before Greene made two free throws to make it 77-71. Greene sandwiched four more free throws between 3-pointers by Funk and Miliner in the final 30 seconds. Illinois State shot 51 percent (29-for-57) and out-rebounded Creighton 39-27 as Gordon pulled down 11. The Bluejays shot 47 percent (30-64).
